    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Visual works where architecture is depicted in outdoor views and interiors and where the architecture is the predominant focus of the painting. In European art, architectural paintings exist as an independent genre developed in the 16th century in Flanders and the Netherlands, and reached its peak in 17th century Dutch painting.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000303/ANET</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000110115/Anet, working group AAT</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Genre binnen de schilderkunst waarbij architectuur van gebouwen afgebeeld wordt, zowel van buiten als van binnen gezien. In de Europese kunst was het een genre dat zich in de 16e eeuw in de Zuidelijke Nederlanden ontwikkelde en zijn hoogtepunt bereikte in de Noordelijke Nederlanden in de 17e eeuw.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000303/ANET</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000110115/Anet, working group AAT</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Obras visuais nas quais a arquitetura é representada em vistas externas e internas, sendo o foco predominante da pintura. Na arte da Europa, pinturas arquitetônicas existem como um gênero independente desenvolvido no século XVI em Flandres e na Holanda, e alcançou seu auge na pintura holandesa do século XVII.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Portuguese</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
